This article describes the setup of ''I<sup>2</sup>C'' ('''I'''nter-'''I'''ntegrated '''C'''ircuit) controllers.

== Hardware detection ==
To choose the right driver, first detect the used I<sup>2</sup>C controllers. You can use [[Hardware detection#lspci|lspci]] for this task:
{{RootCmd|lspci {{!}} grep -i smbus}}

== Installation ==

=== Kernel ===
You need to activate the following kernel options:
{{Kernel||<pre>
Device Drivers  --->
    <*> I2C support  --->
        <*>   I2C device interface
        [*]   Autoselect pertinent helper modules
              I2C Hardware Bus support  --->

                  ''Select the driver for your I2C controller,''
                  ''e.g. for an Intel ICH/PCH controller:''
                  <*> Intel 82801 (ICH/PCH)
</pre>}}

